ETFs in laboratory asset markets

J. Duffy (UC Irvine), J.P. Rabanal (Monash U), O. Rud (Unimelb),

Research question

  • Does the ETFs affect price discovery?

Market Design

  • 3 assets: A, B and C, where \(C= A + B\)
  • T = 15 periods
  • dividend streams:
    • A pays 1 or -1
    • B pays the opposite of A in all periods. Starting from t=8, pays plus 1.
  • \(FV_{{A,t}}= 10\)
  • \(FV_{B,t}=\left\{\begin{array}{ll} 18 & \mbox{for}\ t \leq 8 \\ (T-t+1)10 + 10 & \mbox{for}\ t > 8 \end{array} \right.\)
  • \(FV_{C,t}=\left\{\begin{array}{ll} 28 & \mbox{for}\ t \leq 8 \\ (T-t+1)10 + 20 & \mbox{for}\ t > 8 \end{array} \right.\)

Experimental Design

  • Each session, 9 players, 2 big markets
  • One market is randomly paid
  • In a big market, we have 3 Call Markets (one market per asset)
  • Endowments of (A, B, C,cash) according to type
Endowments
A B C cash
type I 8 2 0 444

Experimental Design

  • UI in oTree (developed by the authors)
  • Subjects from UC Irvine
  • Two pilots run last week

Pilot results

  • 2 sessions
  • One closer to FVs
  • Another with bubbles that do not burst
